text: Van Reed Farmstead is a historic home and farm located in Pine Township, Warren County, Indiana. The farmhouse was built in 1856, and is a large two- story, double pile Greek Revival style brick dwelling. It has a cut stone foundation and a two-story rear wing. Also on the property are the contributing summer kitchen (1856), two well pits (1856), and a Sweitzer barn (1856). Note: This includes , Sketch plans, Site map, and Accompanying photographs It was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 2015. ==References== Category:Farms on the National Register of Historic Places in Indiana Category:Greek Revival houses in Indiana Category:Houses completed in 1856 Category:Buildings and structures in Warren County, Indiana Category:National Register of Historic Places in Warren County, Indiana
